		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Isn't there a tool that converts MID files to MML (MID2MML)?
<br />I've never used NESMUS, but from a quick peek at Bob Rost's website it sort of looked like MML to me. The result might require some manual editing though.
<br />
<br />But honestly, would you really need this for a one-channel song? I've manually transcribed 2-minute long songs with four channels into MML. It may not be a lot of fun, but it doesn't take <strong>that</strong> long, and you get the hang of it pretty quickly.
<br />
<br />And unless you happen to be taking Rost's course and he is forcing you to use NESMUS I think it'd be a wise decision to use a better music creation tool for the NES; like FamiTracker, Nijuu or PPMCK.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
